a. conducts its activities in a country outside the Netherlands; and

b. on the balance sheet date exceeds at least two of the following three criteria:
1. balance sheet total: €20 million;
2. net turnover: €40 million;
3. average number of employees of 250 during the financial year

registration_requirements.data_elements:
Filling out an online registration form is required to register with the online packaging register LUCID. This registration form requires the following information:
- Name, address and contact details of the manufacturer (in particular postcode and town, street and house number, country, telephone number and European or national tax number);
- in the case of an authorisation, name, address and contact details of the authorised representative and the written mandate from the manufacturer;
- details of a natural person authorised to represent the manufacturer;
- national identification number and e-mail address of the manufacturer; in the case of an authorisation, the same details of the authorised representative;
- brand names under which the manufacturer places its packaging on the market;
- details of the packaging that the manufacturer places on the market, declaration that all information in accordance with this paragraph is true.

registration_requirements.responsible_party:
1) entrepreneurs: a) placing products on the market, b) operating a retail trade unit, wholesale trade unit or catering unit offering single-use plastic products, c) recovering or recycling waste arising from products, d) exporting and intra-Community delivery of waste arising from products for the purpose of recovery or recycling;
2) organization (It is a recovery organization - an entity that may partially take over from the entrepreneur his obligations under the contract)
3) authorized representative referred to in Art. 8a section 1;
4) an entrepreneur operating port waste reception facilities or an entrepreneur operating other equivalent collection systems.

regulatory_requirements.trigger:
Being the possessor of the waste, unless covered by exclusion for:
1) producers of: a) municipal waste, b) waste in the form of end-of-life vehicles, if these vehicles were handed over to an entrepreneur running a dismantling station or an entrepreneur running a vehicle collection point, c) who are farmers farming an area of agricultural land below 75 ha, unless they are subject to entry in the register pursuant to Art. 51 section 1, d) construction and demolition waste originating from construction works carried out by natural persons who are not entrepreneurs;
2) natural persons and organizational units other than entrepreneurs who use waste for their own needs, in accordance with Art. 27 section 8 of Act on Waste;
3) an entity conducting activities other than business activities in the field of waste management, which collects packaging waste and waste in the form of used consumer goods, including collection of medicines and medicine packaging by pharmacies, acceptance of used consumer goods in stores, waste collection systems in schools, educational institutions - educational institutions, offices and institutions (unprofessional activities in the field of waste collection);
4) entity: a) engaged in the production, storage, transport or placing on the market of medicated feed or intermediate products, b) which only transports or stores medicated feed or intermediate products only in sealed packages or containers, c) retailing medicated feed for pets - who collects unused or expired medicated feed or intermediate products from entities that only purchase, store or transport medicated feed for use only on their farm, from fur animal keepers and pet keepers.
5) types of waste or quantities of waste specified in the relevant regulation of the Ministry of Climate.

regulatory_requirements.threshold:
Simplified waste records using only waste transfer cards are kept by:
1) entities that: a) produce hazardous waste in an amount of up to 100 kilograms per year, b) produce non-hazardous waste that is not municipal waste in an amount of up to 5 tons per year;
2) waste transporter providing only waste transport services;
3) managing the land surface on which municipal sewage sludge is used for the purposes referred to in Art. 96 section 1 points 1-3.
